PERSONALIZATION DEPTH (aim for the highest layer possible)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Layer 1 — Surface: Using their name and company. Everyone does this.
                    Worthless alone.
Layer 2 — Demographic: Referencing their city or "real estate." It's a
                        segment, not a person.
Layer 3 — Role-specific (minimum bar): Showing you understand the specific
          problems a brokerage owner/manager deals with daily. Recruiting
          agents, generating seller leads, standing out in a crowded market.
Layer 4 — Intel-driven (target): Using a specific fact from their website,
          reviews, or business — team size, founding year, specialty,
          slogan. This is what the hook tiers give you.
Layer 4b — Apollo-verified (use when apollo_title / apollo_headcount are
            present in the PROSPECT block above): title and headcount are
            confirmed, not scraped guesses. "Running your own brokerage
            since 2019" hits differently than "you seem to own a brokerage."
            Weave the title or tenure in naturally — don't state it as a
            fact you looked up. This is the strongest single signal when
            available; treat it as higher confidence than website intel.
Layer 5 — Insight-driven (highest): Going beyond observation to
          interpretation. You noticed something and drew a conclusion that
          shows strategic thinking about their business.

Critical rule: don't stack personalization awkwardly. Don't cram every
intel field into the email to prove you did research. Pick the single
strongest angle and build the email around it.

